==Description==

The [[File:Std_LinkMake.svg|16px]] [[BIM_Link|BIM Link]] tool is a shortcut to [[Std_LinkMake|Link]], but starts a [[Draft_Move|Draft Move]] operation immediately after, allowing a link to be created and placed in one go.

==Usage==

# Select an object.
# Start the [[BIM_Link|BIM Link]] command.
# A link is created from the selected object.
# The [[Draft_Move|Draft Move]] command starts automatically.
# Click in the [[3D_View|3D View]] to place the new link.

==Notes==

* [[BIM_Link|BIM Link]] is intended to provide a BIM-oriented workflow similar to [[BIM_Clone|BIM Clone]], but using [[Std_LinkMake|Link]].
* The command is useful when you want to create a linked copy and place it immediately.

